{
  "message": "Use @import() instead of inline structs for modules\n\nChanged from inlining modules as structs to using Zig's @import():\n- Main file now generates: const mod = @import(\"./mod.zig\")\n- Checks for .build/module.zig before importing\n- Skips external modules gracefully\n- Eliminates duplicate __name__ conflicts\n- Cleaner generated code, better optimization\n\nExample before:\n  pub const test_math = struct { ... }  // 100s of lines inlined\n\nExample after:\n  const test_math = @import(\"./test_math.zig\");  // Clean!\n\nStatus: Nested imports work, allocator detection pending",
